  <description><![CDATA[<p>Explore the snowy settings of Lapland at the Panorama Hotel &amp; Apartments, where unforgettable adventures await. Our 3 or 4 night short breaks, available during December, at the Panorama are a fantastic option for couples, families and friends wanting to get a taste of Lapland this winter. You couldn't ask for a better located hotel, set on top of the Levi fell you'll have wonderful panoramic views of the ski resort, fells and village. Exploring Levi is really easy too, just hop on the Levi Express gondola which is conveniently positioned right next to the hotel. </p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">What's included in our Panorama short break?</h2>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;">Flights departing from London Gatwick, Manchester and Bristol (3-night breaks departing on Sundays and 4-night breaks departing on Wednesdays during December)</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">Short airport transfers </li>
<li style="text-align: left;">3 or 4 nights stay at Panorama Hotel &amp; Apartments on half-board</li>
<li>Festive Feast on your final evening (this replaces your last half-board dinner)</li>
<li>Levi Express Gondola tickets</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: left;">Choose from optional excursions and extras including snowmobiling, husky &amp; reindeer safari, Santa's Elves Hideaway, and thermal suits and boots, are available to add to your arctic getaway. If you opt for a 4-night break you'll also have the option to add a luxury glass igloo overnight stay and a ski taster to your holiday. </p>
<h2>Panorama Hotel and Apartments</h2>
<p>Perched on the Levi Fall, you will enjoy breath-taking views of the surrounding fells and the ski resort's snow-covered slopes. <span> </span><span>Overlooking the Levi Village, the hotel is easily accessible via the </span>Levi Summit gondola, which is accessible from the hotel and runs from 9:30 am to 11 pm, making it very simple to explore the resort. It takes less than five minutes to go to Levi's centre. Additionally, each day of your stay—aside from the day of arrival or departure—you'll receive a complimentary day ticket.</p>
<p>The rooms are the Panorama Hotel are comfortable and spacious and can accommodate additional beds, providing comfort for the whole family. If you want your own space, the Panorama Apartments are a great option, each of the modern apartments has cosy bedrooms and a private sauna - perfect for warming up in after a day of Arctic adventures. After a day of exploring Levi, there are plenty of areas to relax and unwind in. Head up to the Panorama Sky Bar and enjoy the magnificent views of the village and fells with a drink or dig into a sweet treat at the Spiella cafe.  Children can make new-found friends in the play area, while adults unwind in the sauna.  When it comes to dinner, enjoy it with a view - meals are taken in the Panorama Restaurant which features a menu inspired by traditional Lappish cuisine and features locally sourced ingredients.</p>
<h2>Optional Arctic excursions </h2>
<p><span>Whether you're staying 3 or 4 nights you have the option to add on a range of optional pre-bookable excursions to your package. Experience the thrill of driving your own snowmobile through the snowy wilderness, visit Santa in his hideaway home or head on a husky and reindeer safari through the frozen forests. Tick off one of your bucket list items and stay in a glass igloo overnight (only available in our 4-night packages), set back from the resort you'll have a prime spot for the greatest show on earth, the Northern Lights. Have you ever wanted to learn to ski? Opt for a 4-night stay and book our Ski Taster Package to experience the wonderful world of skiing in Finland's best ski resort. </span><span>Remember to add on your thermal suits and boots! </span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
